article.headline: Kennesaw State 83, Jacksonville 76
article.story: KENNESAW, Ga. (AP) -- Shuan Stegall scored 27 points and Golden Ingle added 13 points and 12 assists to lead Kennesaw State to an 83-76 win over Jacksonville on Saturday night. The Owls (7-12, 3-3 Atlantic Sun Conference), who trailed by 10 points twice in the first half, cut the lead to 35-30 before halftime. Then Kennesaw State started the second half with an 8-2 run. Jacksonville (7-9, 3-3) took a 39-38 on a Marcus Allen layup with 18:17 left in the second. But the Owls regained the advantage for good, pushing their lead to eight points over the next five minutes. Ronell Wooten scored 14 points, Michael Nickerson had 12 and Brent Ragsdale added 10 for Kennesaw State. Jesse Kimbrough and Lehmon Colbert each scored 17 points for Jacksonville. Allen added 10 points.
